	<dl>
	<dt>Wrong. I am voting. And to be frank, ...</dt>
	<dd><p>Wrong. I am voting. And to be frank, I think that anyone who falls back on witless second-hand platitudes like "there's no difference between them" or "they're all liars" is betraying our ancestors who fought long and hard - and sometimes died -for the right to vote.</p> <p>Anyone who turns their back on this fantastic achievement demoted themself to the status of a medieval serf.</p> <p>Not apathetic? No - just pathetic.</p>
	<small>
	written 15th Apr 2005 <!--  | <a href="../email/867">Email this
    to a friend</a> | <a
    href="/abuse/?postid=867">abusive?</a> -->
	</small>
	</dd>
	</dl>

<h2><a name="comments"></a>Responses</h2>
<dl>	<dd><a name="comment_854" ></a>
	<p><em><strong>Tom Smith</strong> replies:</em> What absolute nonsense... we haven't come very far from the days of the 'medievil serfs' you describe. The money stays on the top as it always has, you have no say in the way anythings done, you're constantly exploited, manipulated and propagandised... except now we have running water and we get to shop at Tescos.</p> <p>I'm not trying to belittle the achievements made so far, and agree that they are praiseworthy, but lets not stop here....</p>
	<small>
	written 15th Apr 2005 <!-- | <a
    href="/abuse/?postid=867&amp;commentid=854">abusive?</a>
    --> </small>
	</dd>
